balanced LMS cone tristimulus values; <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>L</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>w</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msubsup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle L\'_{w}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/99053ca0e2b7274877f72130e1c8afb3aa388d11" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:3.01ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="L&#039;_{w}" /></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>M</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>w</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msubsup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle M\'_{w}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/66fdbad698e78734f6dcdaec74d50564307a330e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:3.681ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="M&#039;_{w}" /></span>, and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>w</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msubsup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle S\'_{w}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/10aaec3f3cfddf9765cd10735d12402815276622" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.852ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="S&#039;_{w}" /></span> are the tristimulus values of an object believed to be white in the un-color-balanced image, and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>L</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle L\'}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7a5bf7164faabe6b737c3d5269366b5e17f2ac7c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.285ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="L&#039;" /></span>, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>M</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle M\'}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5a3b2ef3304c46b5e7859eec0b1bc057c8eb3f75" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.201ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="M&#039;" /></span>, and <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msup>\n          <mi>S</mi>\n          <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle S\'}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bf9961844d1f539adee019e432dc18aa2a7ede59" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.224ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="S&#039;" /></span> are the tristimulus values of a pixel in the un-color-balanced image.</p>\n<p>Matrices to convert to LMS space were not specified by von Kries, but can be derived from CIE color matching functions and LMS color matching functions when the latter are specified; matrices can also be found in reference books.<sup id="cite_ref-Sharma_12-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Sharma-12">[12]</a></sup></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Scaling_camera_RGB">Scaling camera RGB</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Color_balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Scaling camera RGB">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>By Viggiano\'s measure, and using his model of gaussian camera spectral sensitivities, most camera RGB spaces performed better than either monitor RGB or XYZ.<sup id="cite_ref-Viggiano2004_9-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Viggiano2004-9">[9]</a></sup> If the camera\'s raw RGB values are known, one may use the 3x3 diagonal matrix:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtable rowspacing="4pt" columnspacing="1em">\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mi>R</mi>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mi>G</mi>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mi>B</mi>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n            </mtable>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtable columnalign="center center center" rowspacing="4pt" columnspacing="1em">\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>255</mn>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mo>/</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msubsup>\n                    <mi>R</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>w</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msubsup>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>255</mn>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mo>/</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msubsup>\n                    <mi>G</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>w</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msubsup>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>255</mn>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mo>/</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <msubsup>\n                    <mi>B</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>w</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msubsup>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n            </mtable>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtable rowspacing="4pt" columnspacing="1em">\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>R</mi>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msup>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>G</mi>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msup>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>B</mi>\n                    <mo>&#x2032;</mo>\n                  </msup>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n            </mtable>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\left[{\\begin{array}{c}R\\\\G\\\\B\\end{array}}\\right]=\\left[{\\begin{array}{ccc}255/R\'_{w}&amp;0&amp;0\\\\0&amp;255/G\'_{w}&amp;0\\\\0&amp;0&amp;255/B\'_{w}\\end{array}}\\right]\\left[{\\begin{array}{c}R\'\\\\G\'\\\\B\'\\end{array}}\\right]}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ca82067c07a9a41fede7da69d5ca13be6be5233a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -4.338ex; width:47.837ex; height:9.843ex;" alt="\\left[{\\begin{array}{c}R\\\\G\\\\B\\end{array}}\\right]=\\left[{\\begin{array}{ccc}255/R&#039;_{w}&amp;0&amp;0\\\\0&amp;255/G&#039;_{w}&amp;0\\\\0&amp;0&amp;255/B&#039;_{w}\\end{array}}\\right]\\left[{\\begin{array}{c}R&#039;\\\\G&#039;\\\\B&#039;\\end{array}}\\right]" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and then convert to a working RGB space such as <a href="/wiki/SRGB" title="SRGB">sRGB</a> or <a href="/wiki/Adobe_RGB" class="mw-redirect" title="Adobe RGB">Adobe RGB</a> after balancing.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Preferred_chromatic_adaptation_spaces">Preferred chromatic adaptation spaces</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Color_balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Preferred chromatic adaptation spaces">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Comparisons of images balanced by diagonal transforms in a number of different RGB spaces have identified several such spaces that work better than others, and better than camera or monitor spaces, for chromatic adaptation, as measured by several <a href="/wiki/Color_appearance_model" title="Color appearance model">color appearance models</a>; the systems that performed statistically as well as the best on the majority of the image test sets used were the "Sharp", "Bradford", "CMCCAT", and "ROMM" spaces.<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="General_illuminant_adaptation">General illuminant adaptation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Color_balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: General illuminant adaptation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The best color matrix for adapting to a change in illuminant is not necessarily a diagonal matrix in a fixed color space. It has long been known that if the space of illuminants can be described as a linear model with <i>N</i> basis terms, the proper color transformation will be the weighted sum of <i>N</i> fixed linear transformations, not necessarily consistently diagonalizable.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">[14]</a></sup></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples">Examples</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Color_balance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Examples">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class="thumb tmulti tnone center">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:912px;max-width:912px">\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_neutral.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Neutral light</div>\n</div>\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_warm.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Wb_girl_warm.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_warm.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Wb_girl_warm.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_warm.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Wb_girl_warm.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_warm.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Warm light</div>\n</div>\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_cold.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Wb_girl_cold.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_cold.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Wb_girl_cold.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_cold.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Wb_girl_cold.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_cold.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Cold light</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:left"></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left;text-align:left;background-color:transparent">Comparison of resulted colors as shot by the digital camera for different light qualities (color temperature): Neutral, Warm and Cold.<sup id="cite_ref-photoskop_15-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-photoskop-15">[15]</a></sup></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="thumb tmulti tnone center">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:912px;max-width:912px">\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_neutral.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Wb_girl_neutral.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_neutral.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Setting: As shot</div>\n</div>\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_cloudy.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Setting: Cloudy</div>\n</div>\n<div class="tsingle" style="float:left;margin:1px;width:302px;max-width:302px">\n<div class="thumbimage"><a href="/wiki/File:Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg/300px-Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg" width="300" height="200" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg/450px-Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg/600px-Wb_girl_tungsten.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4746" data-file-height="3164" /></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left">Setting: Tungsten</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:left"></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption" style="clear:left;text-align:left;background-color:transparent">Example of different white balance settings on digital camera for Neutral light.<sup id="cite_ref-photoskop_15-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-photoskop-15">[15]</a></sup></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><sp